Pract1: Configure Routers for syslog and NTP operations
a.	OSPF MD5 authentication
b.	NTP
c.	To log messages to the syslog server
Step 1: Make the topology as per the table and change the name according to the table
Step 2: Off the switch and add the HWIC-2 in both the space in all 3 routers (1941router)
Step 3: Connect the wires according to the addressing table (routers red without clock wire)
Step 4: Give the IP addresses to all the servers and routers
Part1: Configure OSPF MD5 Authentication
R1:
Router(config)#router ospf 1
Router(config-router)#network 192.168.1.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
Router(config-router)#network 10.1.1.0 0.0.0.255 area 0

- Configure OSPF MD5 authentication for all the routers in area 0
Router(config-router)#router ospf 1
Router(config-router)#area 0 authentication message-digest

- Configure the MD5 key for all the routers in area 0.
Router(config-router)#int s0/0/0
Router(config-if)#ip ospf message-digest-key 1 md5 MD5pa55	
Router#show ip ospf interface

R2:
Router(config)#router ospf 1
Router(config-router)#network 10.1.1.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
Router(config-router)#network 10.2.2.0 0.0.0.255 area 0

Router(config-router)#router ospf 1
Router(config-router)#area 0 authentication message-digest
Router(config-router)#int s0/0/0
Router(config-if)#ip ospf message-digest-key 1 md5 MD5pa55
Router(config-if)#int s0/0/1
Router(config-if)#ip ospf message-digest-key 1 md5 MD5pa55
Router#show ip ospf interface

R3: 
Router(config)#router ospf 1
Router(config-router)#network 192.168.3.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
Router(config-router)#network 10.2.2.0 0.0.0.255 area 0

Router(config-router)#router ospf 1
Router(config-router)#area 0 authentication message-digest
Router(config-router)#int s0/0/1
Router(config-if)#ip ospf message-digest-key 1 md5 MD5pa55
Router#show ip ospf interface

Part 2: Configure NTP
-Enable NTP authentication on PC-A.
Go to NTP server-services-NTP-enable-Key:1-Pass:NTPpa55

- Configure R1, R2, and R3 as NTP clients.
R1:
Router(config)#ntp server 192.168.1.5

- Configure routers to update hardware clock.
Router(config)#ntp update-calendar
Router#show clock

- Configure NTP authentication on the routers.
Router(config)#ntp authenticate
Router(config)#ntp trusted-key 1
Router(config)#ntp authentication-key 1 md5 NTPpa55

- Configure routers to timestamp log messages.
Router(config)#service timestamps log datetime msec

Part3: Configure Routers to Log Messages to the Syslog Server
- Configure the routers to identify the remote host (Syslog Server) that will receive logging messages.
Router(config)#logging host 192.168.1.6
Router#show logging

R2:
